com.nokia.dempsy.router
Class Router

java.lang.Object
  com.nokia.dempsy.router.Router
All Implemented Interfaces:
Dispatcher, RoutingStrategy.Outbound.Coordinator
public class Router
extends Object
implements Dispatcher, RoutingStrategy.Outbound.Coordinator

This class implements the routing for all messages leaving a node. Please note: This object is meant to be instantiated and manipulated by the Dempsy orchestrator and not used directly. However, it is important to understand how routing within Dempsy works.

Routing a message to a message processor happens in three stages. Given an ApplicationDefinition that contains many message processor clusters, messages leaving any one Dempsy.Application.Cluster.Node need to be routed to the appropriate message processors in other clusters. The stages are as follows:

  • Using the message's type information (and ClusterDefinition if "destinations" are set) determine the cluster that contains the message processor that the message needs to be sent to.
  • Within the cluster determine the Dempsy.Application.Cluster.Node currently responsible for processing that message using the messages key (MessageKey) and the current RoutingStrategy for that cluster.
  • Once the message is sent to the appropriate Dempsy.Application.Cluster.Node the MpContainer is responsible for routing the message to the appropriate MessageProcessor

    • As mentioned, if the particular cluster that the node that this Router is instantiated in has explicitly defined destinations, then the message routing will be limited to only those destinations.

    A router requires a non-null ApplicationDefinition during construction.
